Code content displayed in drift show, drift diff, and drift list --verbose is syntax-highlighted using a language-agnostic token classifier. Four token types are recognized: comments (line prefixes //, #, --), strings (quoted sequences), keywords (~80 common cross-language words like if, func, return, import), and numbers (numeric literals). Each token type maps to a theme element (code_comment, code_string, code_keyword, code_number). The classifier is deliberately approximate — no language grammar, no block comments, no type inference. False positives in non-code files are acceptable since highlighting is cosmetic. This is language-agnostic by design: no file extension lookup, no per-language configuration. See <ref spec="principles.language_agnostic">language agnostic</ref> and <ref spec="output_impl.tokenizer">the tokenizer</ref>.